[
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Ellicott's Commentary for English Readers",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(46) ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "For had ye believed Moses.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "—The present incredulity springs from that of the past. If they had really believed Moses, they would have seen in the whole spirit of the Pentateuch a manifestation of God, which would have led them to the fuller manifestation in Christ. Worship, and sacrifice, and offering, and priesthood, were all meant to teach. Their very name for “law” (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Thorah",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") meant “instruction.” But they accepted what the senses could know, and never went down beneath this surface to its true significance—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "i.e.,",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " they never ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "believed",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " Moses. We have here, in another form, the thought of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "John 5:39-40",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "For he wrote of me.—See the marginal references; but the thought is not to be confined to these passages.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "For he wrote of me.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—See the marginal references; but the thought is not to be confined to these passages.",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Matthew Henry's Concise Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "5:45-47 Many trust in some form of doctrines or some parties, who no more enter into the real meaning of those doctrines, or the views of the persons whose names they bear, than the Jews did into those of Moses. Let us search and pray over the Scriptures, as intent on finding eternal life; let us observe how Christ is the great subject of them, and daily apply to him for the life he bestows.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Barnes' Notes on the Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Do not think that I will accuse you - Do not suppose that I intend to follow your example. They had accused Jesus of breaking the law of God, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "John 5:16",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". He says that he will not imitate their example, though he implies that he might accuse them.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "To the Father - To God.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "There is one that accuseth you - Moses might be said to accuse or reprove them. He wrote of the Messiah, clearly foretold his coming, and commanded them to hear him. As they did not do it, it might be said that they had disregarded his command; and as Moses was divinely commissioned and had a right to be obeyed, so his command reproved them: they were disobedient and rebellious.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "He wrote of me - He wrote of the Messiah, and I am the Messiah, Genesis 3:15; Genesis 12:3; compare John 8:56; Genesis 49:10; Deuteronomy 18:15. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "He wrote of me - He wrote of the Messiah, and I am the Messiah, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Genesis 3:15",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "; ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Genesis 12:3",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "; compare ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "John 8:56",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "; ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Genesis 49:10",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "; ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Deuteronomy 18:15",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
