  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Matthew Poole's Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " Had you given a hearty credit and understanding assent to Moses, that is, to the writings of Moses, for so the term is oft taken, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Luke 16:31 24:27",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Luke 16:31",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " 24:27",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", you would have received me: as all the law of Moses pointed to and prefigured me, so he in particular wrote of me, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Genesis 3:15 Deu 18:15",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Genesis 3:15",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Deu 18:15",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "For had ye believed Moses,.... The doctrine of Moses, and what he says in his writings: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "ye would have believed me; for there is an agreement between Moses and Christ; Christ is the end of the law of Moses, and in him is the accomplishment of his writings: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "for he wrote of me; in the books written by him, Christ is spoken of, as the seed of the woman, that should bruise the serpent's head; as the seed of Abraham, in whom all nations of the earth should be blessed; as the Shiloh, to whom the gathering of the people should be; and as that prophet, who should be like unto himself, to whom the people of Israel should hearken; and he wrote many things typically of Christ; and indeed, the whole Mosaic economy was typical of Christ, as the epistle to the Hebrews shows: and therefore disbelieving Christ, was disbelieving Moses; who therefore would be an accuser of them, and a witness against them. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "for he wrote of me; in the books written by him, Christ is spoken of, as the seed of the woman, that should bruise the serpent's head; as the seed of Abraham, in whom all nations of the earth should be blessed; as the Shiloh, to whom the gathering of the people should be; and as that prophet, who should be like unto himself, to whom the people of Israel should hearken; and he wrote many things typically of Christ; and indeed, the whole Mosaic economy was typical of Christ, as the epistle to the Hebrews shows: and therefore disbelieving Christ, was disbelieving Moses; who therefore would be an accuser of them, and a witness against them. ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
